<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-06-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-06-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="1188" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1188">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.93/31.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Ambassador</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-06-06">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 6, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>You may instruct consuls to render, whenever it appears to them
                            necessary, such informal good offices as may be possible and as the
                            local authorities may permit to be exercised, to Chinese resident in
                            Mexico.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>